Generator.DefiningQuery:
-- class definitions select z.Tag , z.Parent , z.ClassId [EventClass!1!Id] , z.Category [EventClass!1!Category] , z.Name [EventClass!1!Name] , z.Name [EventClass!1!ClassName] , z.ColId [Col!2!Id] , z.ColName [Col!2!Name] from (
select 1 as Tag , NULL as Parent , e.trace_event_id as ClassId , c.name as Category , e.name as Name , NULL as ColId , NULL as ColName from sys.trace_events e join sys.trace_categories c on e.category_id = c.category_id where c.name = N'Security Audit'
UNION ALL select 2 as Tag , 1 as Parent , e.trace_event_id as ClassId , NULL as Category , NULL as Name , c.trace_column_id , c.name from sys.trace_events e join sys.trace_event_bindings ec on e.trace_event_id = ec.trace_event_id join sys.trace_columns c on ec.trace_column_id = c.trace_column_id join sys.trace_categories cat on e.category_id = cat.category_id where cat.name = N'Security Audit' ) z order by z.ClassId, z.Tag for xml explicit
-- Columns query (so we don't have to keep redefining the membername and have discrepencies select c.trace_column_id [@ColId] , c.name [@ColName] , c.Name [@MemberName] , CASE c.name WHEN N'EventSequence' THEN 'bigint' ELSE c.type_name END [@ColType] , case c.type_name when N'nvarchar' then c.max_size /2 else c.max_size end [@ColMaxSize] from sys.trace_columns c for xml path ('Column')
